wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Gamble (born 21 June 1800) was an English cricketer who was recorded in one first-class match in 1826 when he played for a combined Sheffield and Leicester team, scoring 61 runs in his only innings and holding one catch. Gamble played for Leicester Cricket Club from 1825 to 1829.
